typedef multimap<TileArgNames::tileArgName_t, pair<int, TileArgNames::tileArgName_t> > TileMapFormatDesc::argTransferMap_t [protected]
 

Type of map to use when transferring arguments from the complex feature to the primitives.

First is the name of the argument in the complex feature. Second.first is the index of the primitive in the vector of primitives for that kind of complex feature and second.second is the name of the argument in the primitive.

)  const
 

Returns all parameters needed for the supplied coordinates on all levels.

It is a dangerous function to use, since there can be a lot of parameters.

Parameters:
allParams The parameters will be put here.
coordsBegin The begin iterator for the coordinates.
coordsEnd The end iterator for the coordinates.
extraPixels How many pixels extra that should be added around each coordinate for each detaillevel. This should correspond to the screen size of the device that is used to show the vector map.
layers The layers to get the params for.
useGzip True if gzip should be used.
language The language to use ( for the string maps ).
minScale The minimum scale allowed.
maxScale The maximum scale allowed.
routeID The route id, in case a route should be present.

zoomFactor How much larger each tile should be on the less detailed level.
exchangeTileFactor When to exchange from a less detailed tile to the next tile: scalelevel( i ) + exchangeFactor* ( scalelevel( i + 1) - scalelevel( i ) ) I.e: 1.0 means change to the new tile when the scalelevel is the same as the scalelevel for the next tile. 0.5 means change halways between the less detailed tile and the next tile.
detailLevels Number of detail levels.
